column1:
English translation:
"I am Irish, Irishman; Irishwoman in Ireland and Irishman abroad."

Translation:
"Táinic iaromhn táimhnéill do Suibhne & ro-éirigh  Moling, 'meinic bámar inar ndís slán   síst ag comhrádh friaroileachnóine na conaire' ar an tioprait úd thall. Tiupra tioprat§na Gealta a hainm, úair is meinic notheimbadh n diarbioriar & day biidhisual abideath abroad in Ireland and Irishman abroad."

Translation:
"I am Irishwoman; Irish man woman in Ireland and Irishman abroad."

column2: Iomthúsa na geilte íarsin; robhaoi risin mbliadhain sin ag tathaighidh Moling, Roshoighedh la n-ann co hEss rocháoin Rúaidh, lá oile go Benda biothfhúara Boirche; gidbé díobh sin doshoighedh gach láoi nofritháiledh a n-espurtain gach n-oidhche co Teach Moling. Ro-ordaigh Moling proinn mbig dhó frisin ré sin, dóigh adubairt re bhanchoig ní do bhleaghan na  mbó do thabairt dó. Muirghil as sainm-sidhe, í ba ben do Mhungán do mhuicidhi Moling. Fa coiffeach furechair i n-eatarfhásach na búailedh do ibhe an bhainne sin.
